<p>I have started a long process through a terminal. Is it possible to make the Ubuntu terminal make a sound once the process is complete?
This way, I donâ€™t need to keep checking, but will instead be notified through a sound or another notification.</p>

<p>You can use this some alternatives;</p>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nv">$ </span>your-bash-command <span class="o">&amp;&amp;</span> aplay /path/to/sound.wav  <span class="c"># can also with *.ogg file.</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nv">$ </span>your-bash-command <span class="o">&amp;&amp;</span> paplay /path/to/sound.ogg  <span class="c"># can also with *.wav file.</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nv">$ </span>your-bash-command<span class="p">;</span> spd-say <span class="s2">"done"</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nv">$ </span>your-bash-command <span class="o">&amp;&amp;</span> notify-send <span class="s2">"done"</span>  <span class="c"># without sound</span>
<span class="nv">$ </span>your-bash-command <span class="o">&amp;&amp;</span> notify-send <span class="s2">"Process completed"</span> <span class="s2">"Come back to the terminal, the task is over"</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<hr />

<p>And this script below is modification of that commands above.</p>

<ol>
  <li>Create the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">notif-me.sh</code> file;</li>
</ol>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="c">#!/bin/bash</span>

notify-send <span class="s2">"Process completed"</span> <span class="s2">"Come back to the terminal, the task is over"</span>
spd-say <span class="s2">"My lord, your process hasbeen complete."</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<ol>
  <li>Make it callable in <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">/bin</code></li>
</ol>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">sudo cp </span>notif-me.sh /bin/notif-me<span class="p">;</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<ol>
  <li>Use it;</li>
</ol>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nv">$ </span>your-bash-command<span class="p">;</span> notif-me

<span class="c"># or</span>

<span class="nv">$ </span>your-bash-command <span class="o">&amp;&amp;</span> notif-me
</code></pre></div></div>
